-- TABLE-Australia building approvals fall 3.5 pct in March
-- By Ian Chua
-- Sun May 04, 2014 09:34PM EDT
-- None



SYDNEY, May 5 (Reuters) - Australian approvals to build new homes in March, seasonally adjusted, released by the Australian Bureau of Statistics on Monday.

Seasonally adjustedMar   Private sector houses  9,224 Total houses   9,340 Total private dwellings   15,752Total dwelling units  15,958  Annual change in total approvals to build new homes: +20.0 percent. Forecasts centred on a rise of 1.0 percent on the month for total approvals, a Reuters poll showed.